      "text": "We may cite some of the history of the web and the pressures that have been applied to it by its ferocious growth. But now we leap forward to the draconian effort to retrofit banking grade security over the largeness of the web and thus create the small web that denies the existence of what came before."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "dde6fb79c2a1932e",
      "text": "The large web uses HTTP protocol, except for specific activities such as shopping checkout where common practice is to create a separate server isolated and held to a higher level of payment security. [https://www.pcisecuritystandards.org/ pci]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "b6dafdc83330b1d6",
      "text": "The small web uses the separately authorized HTTPS protocol suggesting that browser users should be confined to servers employing the degree of security once reserved for payment systems. Such concern was motivated by the Snowden revelations that the US signals intelligence agency was spying on US citizens even though that was forbidden."
