    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "297ad0637f311763",
      "text": "A community can choose to host and serve their federated wiki pages in the small web but their community is thus inclosed and cut off from the work of others that preceded them. This is because pages are shared and edited within a single browser tab. Special cross-origin permission headers are required but these have always been provided. But these alone are not enough to allow sharing from the large to the small web."
    },
